		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Xlib</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Xlib</b> is an <a href="/wiki/X_Window_System" title="X Window System">X Window System</a> protocol client <a href="/wiki/Library_(computer_science)" title="Library (computer science)" class="mw-redirect">library</a> in the <a href="/wiki/C_(programming_language)" title="C (programming language)">C programming language</a>. It contains <a href="/wiki/Subroutine" title="Subroutine">functions</a> for interacting with an X <a href="/wiki/Server_(computing)" title="Server (computing)">server</a>. These functions allow <a href="/wiki/Programmer" title="Programmer">programmers</a> to write programs without knowing the details of the <a href="/wiki/Protocol_(computing)" title="Protocol (computing)">protocol</a>. Few applications use Xlib directly; rather, they employ other libraries that use Xlib functions to provide <a href="/wiki/Widget_toolkit" title="Widget toolkit">widget toolkits</a>:</p>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:308px;"><a href="/wiki/File:X-client-libraries.svg" class="image" title="Xlib and other libraries using it"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/X-client-libraries.svg/306px-X-client-libraries.svg.png" width="306" height="189" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">Xlib and other libraries using it</div>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Intrinsics" title="Intrinsics">Intrinsics</a> (Xt)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Xaw" title="Xaw">Athena widget set</a> (Xaw)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Motif_(widget_toolkit)" title="Motif (widget toolkit)">Motif</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/GTK%2B" title="GTK+">GTK+</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Qt_(toolkit)" title="Qt (toolkit)">Qt</a> (X11 version)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Tk_(programming_language)" title="Tk (programming language)" class="mw-redirect">Tk</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Xlib appeared around 1985, and is currently used in <a href="/wiki/GUI" title="GUI" class="mw-redirect">GUIs</a> for many <a href="/wiki/Unix" title="Unix">Unix</a>-like <a href="/wiki/Operating_system" title="Operating system">operating systems</a>.</p>
<p>The <a href="/wiki/XCB" title="XCB">XCB</a> library is an attempt to replace Xlib.</p>
